OL,3,CRogue traders made pensioner buy them
OL,4,Cgold bracelet worth thousands
OL,6,FTwo rogue traders who bullied an
OL,7,Felderly man with dementia into buying
OL,8,Fthem a gold bracelet worth thousands
OL,9,Fhave been jailed.
OL,11,FTommy Aaron Chislett and Shane Lee
OL,12,Ftook the pensioner to purchase the
OL,13,F#3,500 piece as upfront payment for
OL,14,Froof repairs, after banks refused
OL,15,Ftheir cash withdrawals.
OL,17,FThe pair also demanded an extra #1,000
OL,18,Ffrom a couple who had already paid
OL,19,Fthem #300 for gardening work.
