OL,3,CRogue traders made pensioner buy them
OL,4,Cgold bracelet worth thousands
OL,6,FThe man told Chislett and Lee that he
OL,7,Fdid not have the money in the house
OL,8,Fand so he went to a branch of his
OL,9,Flocal bank to withdraw the cash.
OL,11,FHowever, realising the request was
OL,12,Funusual, the bank refused to release
OL,13,Fthe funds.
OL,15,FWhen the pensioner returned empty-
OL,16,Fhanded, the men drove him to a
OL,17,Fdifferent branch of the bank and made
OL,18,Fhim try to withdraw money again.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
