OL,3,CRogue traders made pensioner buy them
OL,4,Cgold bracelet worth thousands
OL,6,FIn the meantime, the bank had
OL,7,Fcontacted the victim's daughter to
OL,8,Falert her of the withdrawal attempt.
OL,10,FUnfortunately, by the time she arrived
OL,11,Fat her father's property, the men had
OL,12,Falready left with her father. Not
OL,13,Fknowing where he was, his daughter
OL,14,Fcontacted the police to report her
OL,15,Ffather as a missing person.
OL,17,FFurther attempts to withdraw money
OL,18,Fwere refused by banks, so Chislett and
OL,19,FLee then took the victim to a
OL,20,Fjewellery shop in Camborne, where he
OL,21,Fwas told to buy them a bracelet.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
