OL,3,CRogue traders made pensioner buy them
OL,4,Cgold bracelet worth thousands
OL,6,FHe paid #3,500 for the bracelet, which
OL,7,Fwas taken from him as payment for the
OL,8,Fwork.
OL,10,FHe was then returned home. The police
OL,11,Farrested Chislett, Lee and the other
OL,12,Flabourer shortly afterwards, but the
OL,13,Fbracelet was never recovered.
OL,15,FRogue traders demanded #1,000 for
OL,16,Fcutting back hedges
OL,18,FThe previous year, Chislett and Lee
OL,19,Fhad delivered flyers to houses in the
OL,20,FTruro area advertising their gardening
OL,21,Fbusiness.
